![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/13dac479-e1ef-45fa-8043-3894c97c037a/e338.jpg?format=original)

From their debut in 2001, Grant Morrison took the X-Men on a mind-bending journey, redefining everything from mutant culture to the very essence of the characters themselves. We'll discuss the introduction of characters like Xorn and Fantomex, the evolution of Jean Grey and Cyclops, and the philosophical underpinnings that made this run so groundbreaking. Plus, we'll delve into how Morrison's unique storytelling style reshaped the superhero landscape and left a lasting impact on X-Men lore in PART ONE of a TWO-PART series covering the whole run!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

